  "title": "Senior Carpenter",
  "description": "<ul><li>Reading and interpreting blueprints, drawings, and sketches to determine specifications and calculate requirements</li><li>Build and fabricate carpentry when given dimensioned drawings </li><li>Cutting and shaping materials and joining them using glue, nails, screws, and bolts.</li><li>Measuring, cutting, and installing various fixtures and millwork for doors, windows, ceiling panels, staircases, decking, furniture, etc.</li><li>Advising clients on the best materials and implementation </li><li>Adhering to safety and health regulations </li><li>Proficient in operating of tools and machinery</li><li>Collaborating with other carpenters, contractors and designers to execute per requirements</li><li>Troubleshooting and repairing defects per customer requests </li></ul><p><br />Working hours: Monday - Saturday (9am - 6pm) <br />Willing to work on Sundays and Public Holidays where necessary <br /></p>",
